rtain minority ethnic groups in ancient southern China."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Blanco","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Manuel, Juan, Carlos, Jorge, Luis, Raul, Francisco, Miguel, Julio, Pedro, Jesus.","Spanish: nickname for a man with white or fair hair or a pale complexion, from <i>blanco</i> ‘white’.","Italian (Sicily): variant of   Bianco  , perhaps influenced by French <i>blanc</i> or Spanish <i>blanco</i> (see 1 above)."],"variants":[{"name":"Bianco","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Vito, Angelo, Salvatore, Carmine, Antonio, Rocco, Aniello, Francesco, Luca, Luigi, Pasquale, Sal.","Italian: from <i>bianco</i> ‘white’ (of ancient Germanic origin; compare Old High German <i>blanc</i> ‘bright, shining, white, beautiful’), originally applied as a nickname for a man with white or fair hair or a pale complexion, or for someone who habitually wore white, especially in jousting or other competitions, and later used as a personal name. Compare   Lo Bianco  ."]},{"name":"Blanca","meanings":["Spanish: from the feminine form of   Blanco   ‘white’."]}]},{"name":"Dama","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Mainly North American: of unknown origin, perhaps a transferred use of a surname that is fairly common in the United States. This may be of Irish origin, although the surname is not known in Ireland. <i>Dana</i> or <i>Ana</i> was the name of an ancient Irish fertility goddess, and this was also used in medieval times as a girl's name, However, it is not clear whether there is any connection between this name and the modern given name, which is sometimes also used as a feminine form of   Dan   or   Daniel .  Modern use as a boy's given name began in honour of  Richard Henry Dana  (  1815–82 ), author of Two Years before the Mast, who supported the rights of fugitive slaves before and during the Civil War. The popularity of the given name was increased by the fame of the film star  Dana Andrews  (  1909–92 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Dama En Blanco had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Walter Loudham I. She died in 1273, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"–1273":"–1273","1225–1272":"1225–1272","1242–1306":"1242–1306","1253–1305":"1253–1305","1305":"1305","1225":"1225","16 Oct 1272":"16. oktoober 1272","1242":"1242","1253":"1253","1273":"1273","1272":"1272","1306":"1306","Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England":"Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England","Lowdham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Lowdham, Nottinghamshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–1273":"–1273","1225–1272":"1225–1272","1242–1306":"1242–1306","1253–1305":"1253–1305","1305":"1305","1225":"1225","16 Oct 1272":"16. lokakuuta 1272","1242":"1242","1253":"1253","1273":"1273","1272":"1272","1306":"1306","Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England":"Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England","Lowdham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Lowdham, Nottinghamshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–1273":"–1273","1225–1272":"1225–1272","1242–1306":"1242–1306","1253–1305":"1253–1305","1305":"1305","1225":"1225","16 Oct 1272":"16 octobre 1272","1242":"1242","1253":"1253","1273":"1273","1272":"1272","1306":"1306","Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England":"Southwell, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre","Lowdham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Lowdham, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Dama En Blanco a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Walter Loudham I. Elle est décédée en 1273, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"–1273":"–1273","1225–1272":"1225–1272","1242–1306":"1242–1306","1253–1305":"1253–1305","1305":"1305","1225":"1225","16 Oct 1272":"16. Oktober 1272","1242":"1242","1253":"1253","1273":"1273","1272":"1272","1306":"1306","Southwell, Nottinghams